1
00:00:00,120 --> 00:00:07,000
Characters, actions, places, occupations,
and events in this series

2
00:00:07,106 --> 00:00:10,020
are fictional and created
for entertainment purposes only.

3
00:00:10,122 --> 00:00:14,675
They are not intended to urge
or promote any behavior in the series.

4
00:00:14,717 --> 00:00:17,170
Viewer discretion is advised.

5
00:00:17,558 --> 00:00:21,004
Your father may be gone,
but his debt isn’t.

6
00:00:21,460 --> 00:00:22,797
You gotta pay for it.

7
00:00:23,137 --> 00:00:24,496
I think Kaye is Mr. Kill.

8
00:00:24,670 --> 00:00:26,297
The murderer is trying to communicate

9
00:00:26,561 --> 00:00:29,980
by leaving clues in the crime scenes
in a way that no one else would notice.

10
00:00:30,217 --> 00:00:33,099
I think the next victim is going to be

11
00:00:34,030 --> 00:00:35,900
a rule-bending defense attorney.

12
00:00:36,057 --> 00:00:37,500
According to the first two cases…

13
00:00:37,924 --> 00:00:39,300
His theory might be right.

14
00:00:39,640 --> 00:00:42,402
You must stay where I can see you 24/7.

15
00:00:43,284 --> 00:00:45,050
At least until we find that lawyer.

16
00:00:50,720 --> 00:00:52,401
You haven’t eaten anything
since this morning.

17
00:00:52,712 --> 00:00:53,398
Eat.

18
00:01:04,339 --> 00:01:04,998
What?

19
00:01:05,204 --> 00:01:07,099
Can you only stomach instant noodles?

20
00:01:19,509 --> 00:01:21,500
2 a.m. is hardly a good time for dinner.

21
00:01:26,432 --> 00:01:27,798
As a cop,

22
00:01:29,057 --> 00:01:30,900
I never know what’s going to happen next.

23
00:01:32,831 --> 00:01:36,802
Maybe I have to chase after
a criminal in five minutes.

24
00:01:38,651 --> 00:01:40,400
If I don’t eat now when I can,

25
00:01:41,370 --> 00:01:42,903
how will I be able to catch bad guys?

26
00:01:47,700 --> 00:01:50,801
I’m not a manga artist like you.

27
00:01:51,874 --> 00:01:53,499
You can get up whenever you want,

28
00:01:53,758 --> 00:01:55,297
go to bed whenever you want.

29
00:01:56,580 --> 00:01:58,801
Like… Why are you throwing shade?

30
00:02:29,013 --> 00:02:30,001
What was that for?

31
00:02:30,515 --> 00:02:32,019
My coffee’s spilled now, don’t you see?

32
00:02:34,730 --> 00:02:35,502
Sorry.

33
00:02:35,613 --> 00:02:37,600
I forgot I’m cuffed.

34
00:02:38,140 --> 00:02:39,200
I’m not used to this yet.

35
00:02:43,062 --> 00:02:43,797
Please.

36
00:03:00,880 --> 00:03:01,934
Are you messing with me?

37
00:03:02,272 --> 00:03:03,192
Of course not.

38
00:03:03,210 --> 00:03:04,897
I just don’t want you spilling
your coffee again.

39
00:03:05,170 --> 00:03:06,096
Please have a sip.

40
00:04:31,245 --> 00:04:32,097
It’s not him.

41
00:04:36,355 --> 00:04:38,998
And what about this guy?

42
00:04:39,550 --> 00:04:40,198
No, sir.

43
00:04:43,146 --> 00:04:44,447
-Him?
-No, sir.

44
00:05:03,377 --> 00:05:04,019
Yes.

45
00:05:06,220 --> 00:05:06,897
Sir.

46
00:05:07,505 --> 00:05:08,497
It’s not him either.

47
00:05:19,220 --> 00:05:20,801
Alright. Let’s keep looking.

48
00:05:30,013 --> 00:05:30,800
(Inspector.)

49
00:05:31,250 --> 00:05:34,302
(The missing lawyers are,
one by one, making contact.)

50
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:36,297
(Except for Attorney Komkrit.)

51
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:38,902
Okay.

52
00:05:39,502 --> 00:05:40,795
I’ll check up on him.

53
00:05:45,640 --> 00:05:46,303
Inspector.

54
00:05:46,425 --> 00:05:47,195
I…

55
00:05:48,023 --> 00:05:48,797
I need to pee.

56
00:05:50,170 --> 00:05:51,699
What? What was that?

57
00:05:52,583 --> 00:05:54,699
I said I need to pee.

58
00:05:55,346 --> 00:05:57,600
Ugh… Bad timing.

59
00:06:23,251 --> 00:06:23,977
Thank you.

60
00:06:24,448 --> 00:06:25,204
Hold on.

61
00:06:28,211 --> 00:06:28,952
What?

62
00:06:29,324 --> 00:06:30,296
Inspector.

63
00:06:30,648 --> 00:06:33,280
I’m literally just going to the toilet.
Do you need to have me cuffed?

64
00:06:34,951 --> 00:06:35,899
Just come on.

65
00:06:46,160 --> 00:06:47,902
Hurry up. I don’t have all day.

66
00:06:54,260 --> 00:06:55,002
Hey.

67
00:06:56,540 --> 00:06:57,201
Hey!

68
00:06:57,644 --> 00:07:00,096
If you’re in such a rush,

69
00:07:00,219 --> 00:07:02,019
why not just uncuff me?

70
00:07:07,107 --> 00:07:07,797
Hey.

71
00:07:08,090 --> 00:07:10,196
You seriously expect me
to just pee like this?

72
00:07:13,033 --> 00:07:13,850
Well, then, let’s go.

73
00:07:14,295 --> 00:07:15,097
Wait.

74
00:07:15,532 --> 00:07:16,899
Are you out of your mind?

75
00:07:16,982 --> 00:07:17,900
Who the hell would be able to pee

76
00:07:17,923 --> 00:07:19,797
with his hand cuffed
to someone else like this?

77
00:07:21,212 --> 00:07:22,999
So you’re not gonna pee?

78
00:07:24,621 --> 00:07:25,500
Then let’s just go.

79
00:07:25,520 --> 00:07:26,501
Wait, wait.

80
00:07:28,587 --> 00:07:29,500
I’ll pee.

81
00:07:41,681 --> 00:07:42,596
Inspector.

82
00:07:43,536 --> 00:07:45,601
What if I have to go number two?

83
00:07:46,768 --> 00:07:47,799
What do we do?

84
00:07:54,770 --> 00:07:56,196
We’ll think about that when that happens.

85
00:07:56,460 --> 00:07:57,400
Just do your business.

86
00:08:43,821 --> 00:08:45,500
If you’re just messing with me,

87
00:08:46,313 --> 00:08:47,500
I won’t let you off the hook.

88
00:08:48,821 --> 00:08:49,503
Listen.

89
00:08:49,640 --> 00:08:51,298
If I really wanted to do that,

90
00:08:51,850 --> 00:08:53,695
I wouldn’t waste my time
coming along with you.

91
00:08:58,580 --> 00:09:01,201
But honestly, I wouldn’t mind
waiting in the car.

92
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:04,803
If we have another body
because you’re stalling for time,

93
00:09:05,181 --> 00:09:06,298
It’ll be on you.

94
00:09:07,811 --> 00:09:08,496
What?

95
00:09:09,257 --> 00:09:11,095
What do you want me to do?

96
00:09:15,810 --> 00:09:16,701
Climb inside?

97
00:09:47,346 --> 00:09:48,603
Wait, hold up.

98
00:09:49,420 --> 00:09:51,387
Just now, don’t you think
that was too convenient for you

99
00:09:51,408 --> 00:09:53,000
to just blame me?

100
00:09:53,577 --> 00:09:57,699
You think I’m okay my manga is used
as death sentences for these victims?

101
00:09:58,277 --> 00:10:01,295
You should know that way better than me.

102
00:10:26,812 --> 00:10:27,898
The door’s unlocked.

103
00:10:48,950 --> 00:10:50,021
Don’t touch anything.

104
00:10:50,955 --> 00:10:51,797
I know that.

105
00:10:59,975 --> 00:11:02,798
The lights and the AC are left on.

106
00:11:04,350 --> 00:11:07,302
Who would leave them running
during the day?

107
00:11:09,220 --> 00:11:10,400
Well, that’s not always true.

108
00:11:10,770 --> 00:11:11,800
Rich people…

109
00:11:12,244 --> 00:11:14,610
They wouldn't be above paying
for their comfort, you know?

110
00:11:16,240 --> 00:11:19,296
It’s not like they’re bothered
paying extra on their electricity bill.

111
00:12:00,368 --> 00:12:02,902
Maybe he was taken while having dinner.

112
00:12:04,070 --> 00:12:06,530
His secretary hasn’t been able
to reach him since Friday, that means…

113
00:12:08,129 --> 00:12:10,395
He’s been missing three days.

114
00:12:10,990 --> 00:12:11,730
Yeah?

115
00:12:14,816 --> 00:12:18,398
A single lawyer
living alone in a big house.

116
00:12:19,840 --> 00:12:21,648
If he had been missing for three days,

117
00:12:22,442 --> 00:12:24,798
no one would suspect anything.

118
00:12:40,827 --> 00:12:41,530
Wait…

119
00:12:42,310 --> 00:12:43,010
Hold on.

120
00:12:45,024 --> 00:12:50,019
What if the murderer didn’t just mean to
set up the bodies like in my manga?

121
00:12:52,715 --> 00:12:54,196
We forgot something important.

122
00:12:55,704 --> 00:13:00,570
The locations might not be
the exact locations in the manga.

123
00:13:02,264 --> 00:13:03,304
But they look the same.

124
00:13:07,356 --> 00:13:08,200
For example…

125
00:13:08,450 --> 00:13:11,603
The first murder happens
in an abandoned warehouse.

126
00:13:13,714 --> 00:13:17,298
In Nekros, the crime scene
is also an abandoned warehouse.

127
00:13:18,750 --> 00:13:19,800
The second murder,

128
00:13:20,297 --> 00:13:22,398
in Nekros,

129
00:13:24,230 --> 00:13:25,497
happens in an empty field.

130
00:13:31,224 --> 00:13:36,024
(Chapter 14 of Nekros
is about a famous lawyer.)

131
00:13:39,557 --> 00:13:40,499
I get it now.

132
00:13:43,308 --> 00:13:46,098
Where does the murder
take place in Chapter 14?

133
00:13:53,856 --> 00:13:54,700
Warehouse…

134
00:13:55,916 --> 00:13:58,800
In Chapter 14 of Nekros,
the crime scene is…

135
00:14:00,100 --> 00:14:01,299
A warehouse by the pier.

136
00:14:03,458 --> 00:14:04,104
Nop.

137
00:14:04,265 --> 00:14:07,699
Send me all locations of warehouses
by the pier near Komkrit’s house.

138
00:14:08,828 --> 00:14:10,303
I’ll check the first one.

139
00:14:10,763 --> 00:14:13,604
Get some local police offices
to check out the other two.

140
00:14:18,941 --> 00:14:19,797
Hang on tight.

141
00:15:01,056 --> 00:15:01,975
Stay behind me.

142
00:15:04,570 --> 00:15:05,299
Yes.

143
00:16:54,309 --> 00:16:54,996
Hey.

144
00:16:57,109 --> 00:16:57,998
You alright?

145
00:17:27,920 --> 00:17:30,050
He’s likely been dead
for no less than a couple hours.

146
00:17:31,012 --> 00:17:32,490
His blood hasn’t fully coagulated,

147
00:17:33,270 --> 00:17:34,700
but rigor mortis has begun to set in.

148
00:17:35,720 --> 00:17:37,799
The murderer likely hasn’t left
the crime scene that long ago.

149
00:17:59,089 --> 00:18:00,104
What about him?

150
00:18:02,946 --> 00:18:03,797
Kaye?

151
00:18:04,899 --> 00:18:07,100
Is he still a suspect?

152
00:18:12,330 --> 00:18:13,035
No.

153
00:18:13,870 --> 00:18:14,803
He didn’t do it.

154
00:18:16,160 --> 00:18:17,497
He was with me the entire time.

155
00:18:40,329 --> 00:18:41,304
Drink some water.

156
00:18:52,919 --> 00:18:54,102
What are you thinking?

157
00:19:00,407 --> 00:19:01,304
I just…

158
00:19:02,997 --> 00:19:04,600
I just want to go home and clean up.

159
00:19:08,150 --> 00:19:09,127
We’re almost done here.

160
00:19:11,600 --> 00:19:12,800
I’ll give you a ride home.

161
00:19:20,803 --> 00:19:21,695
I’m sorry.

162
00:19:24,991 --> 00:19:27,052
Sorry? For what?

163
00:19:29,020 --> 00:19:31,097
For what I said at Komkrit’s house.

164
00:19:36,537 --> 00:19:37,473
But you…

165
00:19:39,218 --> 00:19:40,996
You might be right.

166
00:19:46,692 --> 00:19:47,978
I drew those panels.

167
00:19:50,196 --> 00:19:51,978
I even came up with the methods.

168
00:19:54,460 --> 00:19:55,498
Abandoned warehouse.

169
00:19:57,230 --> 00:19:58,300
Empty field.

170
00:19:59,978 --> 00:20:01,098
Because I…

171
00:20:01,590 --> 00:20:03,050
I… drew—

172
00:20:03,996 --> 00:20:05,097
Hey. Take it easy.

173
00:20:12,089 --> 00:20:13,002
Where’s your pill?

174
00:20:26,260 --> 00:20:26,967
Swallow.

175
00:20:27,302 --> 00:20:27,901
Swallow.

176
00:20:28,080 --> 00:20:29,097
Take it easy.

177
00:20:29,767 --> 00:20:30,901
Take a deep breath.

178
00:20:31,399 --> 00:20:32,297
Take a deep breath.

179
00:20:34,155 --> 00:20:35,304
Focus, Kaye.

180
00:20:35,829 --> 00:20:36,647
Focus.

181
00:20:39,340 --> 00:20:39,975
Listen to me.

182
00:20:40,490 --> 00:20:42,000
You didn’t kill anyone.

183
00:20:43,843 --> 00:20:46,800
It’s the murderer who imitates your work.

184
00:20:47,823 --> 00:20:48,701
You didn’t do it.

185
00:20:52,072 --> 00:20:56,400
And everything that happens
isn’t your fault.

186
00:20:58,889 --> 00:21:02,602
But if your guilt makes you want
to take responsibility for it…

187
00:21:07,059 --> 00:21:07,981
Work with me.

188
00:21:14,080 --> 00:21:15,566
Work–work with you?

189
00:21:16,709 --> 00:21:17,600
You mean…

190
00:21:24,370 --> 00:21:25,301
From now on,

191
00:21:25,977 --> 00:21:27,977
you’re no longer a suspect.

192
00:21:29,330 --> 00:21:34,400
You’re going to be a special consultant
to my Nekros Investigation Team.

193
00:21:38,744 --> 00:21:39,503
Right now,

194
00:21:39,900 --> 00:21:43,301
you’re the only person who knows
what’s going on in the murderer’s head.

195
00:21:46,096 --> 00:21:48,501
If you want your guilt to fade away,

196
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:51,251
work with me.

197
00:21:52,610 --> 00:21:53,596
Let’s catch this guy.

198
00:22:25,107 --> 00:22:26,395
You should go on and take a rest.

199
00:22:26,481 --> 00:22:28,040
I’ll call you if anything comes up.

200
00:23:50,375 --> 00:23:52,700
Oh, you’re here.

201
00:23:53,400 --> 00:23:54,499
Hello, Aunt Sri.

202
00:23:55,098 --> 00:23:57,304
I’m sorry I’m late.

203
00:23:57,415 --> 00:23:58,796
Something came up.

204
00:23:59,390 --> 00:24:03,304
I’ll wire you your salary
first thing tomorrow morning.

205
00:24:03,366 --> 00:24:05,170
I’m sorry I can’t pay you on time
this month.

206
00:24:05,252 --> 00:24:07,500
It’s alright. I understand.

207
00:24:08,055 --> 00:24:09,601
I’m going home,

208
00:24:09,864 --> 00:24:12,298
but you know you can ring me up anytime.

209
00:24:13,163 --> 00:24:14,202
Thank you.

210
00:25:10,421 --> 00:25:11,100
Dad.

211
00:25:11,680 --> 00:25:14,499
I’m sorry I’ve been away for so many days.

212
00:25:14,528 --> 00:25:16,603
I was kind of busy.

213
00:25:37,370 --> 00:25:38,501
How are you doing, Dad?

214
00:25:39,536 --> 00:25:40,796
Do you sleep well?

215
00:25:48,679 --> 00:25:50,700
Let’s get you cleaned up, shall we?

216
00:26:20,520 --> 00:26:24,130
PAID

217
00:26:42,800 --> 00:26:46,930
K-CUPID = MR. KILL
(NEKROS CREATOR)

218
00:26:49,427 --> 00:26:50,295
My God.

219
00:26:57,700 --> 00:26:58,351
Hey.

220
00:26:58,880 --> 00:27:00,997
How many times did I tell you
not to barge in?

221
00:27:01,464 --> 00:27:03,702
Wait, is this true?

222
00:27:04,016 --> 00:27:05,978
K-Cupid is Mr. Kill?

223
00:27:06,495 --> 00:27:07,980
What is he like in real life?

224
00:27:39,583 --> 00:27:43,501
(Editor, I’ll send you the manuscript
of the new chapter tonight.)

225
00:28:11,606 --> 00:28:15,500
You told me Kaye draws
the saddest look in his characters’ eyes.

226
00:28:15,815 --> 00:28:19,900
His own eyes… are
about a hundred times sadder.

227
00:28:25,420 --> 00:28:26,800
Come on and go away already.

228
00:28:27,858 --> 00:28:28,599
Wait.

229
00:28:29,245 --> 00:28:30,600
I have one more question.

230
00:28:31,373 --> 00:28:33,701
Does he have anything to do
with the murderer?

231
00:28:48,800 --> 00:28:50,498
K-Cupid’s Love in the Wind?

232
00:28:50,739 --> 00:28:51,981
I like this manga, too.

233
00:28:52,218 --> 00:28:53,000
You do?

234
00:28:53,503 --> 00:28:54,801
I love this manga.

235
00:28:59,942 --> 00:29:01,397
If I were to tell you

236
00:29:02,339 --> 00:29:05,500
that K-Cupid is the same artist
who writes Nekros,

237
00:29:06,495 --> 00:29:07,500
would you believe me?

238
00:29:07,583 --> 00:29:08,301
Huh?

239
00:29:11,369 --> 00:29:15,400
Are you saying Kaye is Mr. Kill, Praew?

240
00:29:20,908 --> 00:29:21,598
Boss.

241
00:29:21,793 --> 00:29:22,427
Hmm?

242
00:29:22,564 --> 00:29:23,239
Yeah?

243
00:29:23,316 --> 00:29:26,850
We’ve just been informed
Nekros killed a third victim.

244
00:29:27,975 --> 00:29:28,996
The victim is…

245
00:29:29,254 --> 00:29:30,680
Attorney Komkrit Nopparakkul.

246
00:29:30,700 --> 00:29:31,403
What?

247
00:29:32,102 --> 00:29:32,999
Attorney Komkrit?

248
00:29:33,120 --> 00:29:33,901
Yes.

249
00:29:34,436 --> 00:29:35,201
Guys.

250
00:29:35,673 --> 00:29:36,999
That’s our scoop now.

251
00:29:37,266 --> 00:29:38,351
Stop whatever you’re doing.

252
00:29:38,368 --> 00:29:39,977
Let’s make a graphic for this news.

253
00:29:41,080 --> 00:29:42,099
Attorney Komkrit…

254
00:29:42,276 --> 00:29:44,101
Isn’t he the lawyer
who only took on high-profile cases?

255
00:29:44,970 --> 00:29:45,900
Girls.

256
00:29:47,094 --> 00:29:49,974
If you have any ideas,
feel free to let me know.

257
00:29:50,558 --> 00:29:51,497
Of course.

258
00:29:59,781 --> 00:30:03,598
In Nekros, the murderer chooses
to kill only bad guys.

259
00:30:04,290 --> 00:30:05,797
Like in the previous two cases.

260
00:30:07,068 --> 00:30:09,796
That means this lawyer
could be dirty, too.

261
00:30:12,567 --> 00:30:13,603
Oh.

262
00:30:13,978 --> 00:30:15,098
Attorney Komkrit.

263
00:30:15,750 --> 00:30:18,701
The lawyer defending the rich kid charged
with manslaughter while drunk driving.

264
00:30:18,988 --> 00:30:20,700
Komkrit. Komkrit…

265
00:30:21,930 --> 00:30:23,900
They really are untouchable, huh.

266
00:30:25,260 --> 00:30:27,266
That’s why a monster like Nekros exists.

267
00:30:28,880 --> 00:30:32,899
A monster who will rebalance
the tipped scale.

268
00:30:33,977 --> 00:30:36,210
Oh, that was nice.

269
00:30:36,887 --> 00:30:38,487
Write it down! I bet Thun’s gonna love it.

270
00:30:38,519 --> 00:30:39,604
-You think?
-Yes.

271
00:30:41,700 --> 00:30:43,095
We have a tag line!

272
00:30:49,340 --> 00:30:53,298
There’s been a third victim
of the serial murder case, Nekros.

273
00:30:53,554 --> 00:30:56,997
The latest victim is none other than
the famous lawyer, Mr. Komkrit,

274
00:30:57,101 --> 00:30:59,890
the man who’s been lauded
as ‘the wizard of the legal world.’

275
00:31:00,170 --> 00:31:03,497
(Netizens are digging up dirt
on all three victims.)

276
00:31:03,520 --> 00:31:09,210
(The underground manga turned murderer
Nekros is being praised for its vigilante.)

277
00:31:09,485 --> 00:31:13,610
(In a world where justice is too costly
for normal people to afford,)

278
00:31:13,725 --> 00:31:17,980
(many people have been waiting
for someone, or some monster,)

279
00:31:18,232 --> 00:31:21,300
(to tip the balance back
on the scale of justice.)

280
00:31:21,690 --> 00:31:22,851
(One thing is certain:)

281
00:31:22,901 --> 00:31:25,290
(As long as the police fail
to catch this murderer,)

282
00:31:25,676 --> 00:31:28,896
(many people will have to sleep
with one eye open.)

283
00:31:59,750 --> 00:32:03,503
(In a world where justice is too costly
for normal people to afford…)

284
00:32:03,886 --> 00:32:04,900
You’re finally here, tiger.

285
00:32:05,652 --> 00:32:06,603
Hello, Uncle.

286
00:32:08,360 --> 00:32:09,095
Here.

287
00:32:10,655 --> 00:32:11,704
Have coffee with me.

288
00:32:11,950 --> 00:32:12,697
Thank you.

289
00:32:12,825 --> 00:32:15,397
(As long as the police fail
to catch this murderer,)

290
00:32:15,575 --> 00:32:17,498
(many people will have to sleep—)

291
00:32:20,606 --> 00:32:23,701
So it’s confirmed
to be a serial murder case.

292
00:32:24,605 --> 00:32:25,981
Forensics just came back with the report.

293
00:32:26,332 --> 00:32:27,203
So, yes.

294
00:32:29,310 --> 00:32:30,695
This is a big case.

295
00:32:31,283 --> 00:32:33,002
The press is shining a spotlight on it.

296
00:32:33,408 --> 00:32:35,598
And there will be a lot of pressure
from the public, too.

297
00:32:36,710 --> 00:32:37,600
You sure you got this?

298
00:32:40,470 --> 00:32:43,799
You know what people think of me, Uncle.

299
00:32:45,159 --> 00:32:46,301
I’m just…

300
00:32:48,553 --> 00:32:49,980
The son of a dirty cop.

301
00:32:52,347 --> 00:32:55,900
I want to prove
that I’m not like my father.

302
00:32:58,830 --> 00:32:59,983
I promise, Uncle,

303
00:33:00,781 --> 00:33:02,295
I’ll see this case through.

304
00:33:04,310 --> 00:33:07,796
If there’s anything you need my help with,
just let me know.

305
00:33:08,822 --> 00:33:10,203
I’m always on your side.

306
00:33:11,607 --> 00:33:12,300
Yes, sir.

307
00:33:33,687 --> 00:33:35,298
I’ve looked through it three times, sir,

308
00:33:35,734 --> 00:33:37,203
and I don’t see any clues.

309
00:33:38,230 --> 00:33:39,898
Maybe he didn’t leave any this time?

310
00:33:41,070 --> 00:33:43,598
A serial killer like him is
always obsessed with patterns.

311
00:33:44,262 --> 00:33:45,972
There’s no way he didn’t leave his M.O.

312
00:33:51,040 --> 00:33:51,796
Sir.

313
00:33:52,510 --> 00:33:55,097
The lab report on the pen stuck on
the victim’s chest just came back.

314
00:34:01,490 --> 00:34:04,001
His relative insists the pen
didn’t belong to Komkrit.

315
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:07,200
But there are also no fingerprints.

316
00:34:20,652 --> 00:34:21,983
I’m sorry I’m late.

317
00:34:26,620 --> 00:34:28,454
We’re waiting for you. Come on in.

318
00:34:34,820 --> 00:34:36,701
Do you know what this message means?

319
00:34:39,520 --> 00:34:41,490
"ENEMIES FOR STRENGTH, FRIENDS FOR HEART"

320
00:34:46,190 --> 00:34:48,997
I think it is said by one of the victims
in Nekros.

321
00:34:49,335 --> 00:34:51,696
But I don’t remember which one.

322
00:34:52,716 --> 00:34:53,402
Nop.

323
00:34:53,640 --> 00:34:55,699
Dig up the Nekros files we recovered
and show them to Kaye.

324
00:34:55,972 --> 00:34:56,698
Yes, sir.

325
00:35:06,955 --> 00:35:08,401
I found it.

326
00:35:10,197 --> 00:35:13,980
The victim in Chapter 18 of Nekros
is a dirty politician.

327
00:35:14,849 --> 00:35:15,978
He’s a two-faced man.

328
00:35:20,040 --> 00:35:21,850
“Enemies give us strength.”

329
00:35:21,984 --> 00:35:23,975
“Real friends give us courage.”

330
00:35:24,378 --> 00:35:28,301
It’s something
the victim of this chapter says a lot.

331
00:35:30,741 --> 00:35:31,637
And…

332
00:35:39,970 --> 00:35:41,100
That’s not everything.

333
00:35:41,760 --> 00:35:42,803
The files are broken.

334
00:35:43,410 --> 00:35:44,798
This is all we could recover.

335
00:35:49,889 --> 00:35:52,697
Do you remember
how the rest of Chapter 18 goes?

336
00:35:55,836 --> 00:35:57,900
I might need to reread
the beginning again.

337
00:35:58,161 --> 00:35:59,396
Maybe it’ll jog my memory.

338
00:36:04,786 --> 00:36:09,720
At least we might be able to find out
who the next victim is going to be.

339
00:36:17,791 --> 00:36:20,700
Read through their profiles
and you just know they’re rotten.

340
00:36:21,940 --> 00:36:23,551
Of course, our country is going nowhere

341
00:36:24,698 --> 00:36:27,360
if these scums are sitting in our parliament.

342
00:36:31,356 --> 00:36:32,102
Sir.

343
00:36:33,150 --> 00:36:34,501
I’ve checked.

344
00:36:35,340 --> 00:36:39,400
No politicians have been reported missing
these past few days.

345
00:36:40,049 --> 00:36:41,400
This could mean two things:

346
00:36:42,040 --> 00:36:42,899
First,

347
00:36:44,107 --> 00:36:45,598
the killer hasn’t started.

348
00:36:46,070 --> 00:36:48,398
Second, we’re on the wrong path.

349
00:36:59,550 --> 00:37:00,502
Whoa, Inspector.

350
00:37:02,158 --> 00:37:03,595
This guy tops the list.

351
00:37:04,329 --> 00:37:04,997
Look.

352
00:37:07,530 --> 00:37:09,600
He was recently involved with
the Chinese syndicate.

353
00:37:09,870 --> 00:37:11,400
But the moment his charges were dropped,

354
00:37:11,485 --> 00:37:13,320
he immediately builds his image back up
by turning to religion.

355
00:37:13,400 --> 00:37:15,269
(As long as we believe in
doing the right thing,)

356
00:37:15,293 --> 00:37:17,290
(our good deeds will protect us.)

357
00:37:17,780 --> 00:37:18,458
Who is he?

358
00:37:18,819 --> 00:37:20,102
That’s MP Jaratphong.

359
00:37:21,023 --> 00:37:23,974
If I was Nekros, he would be
the top name on my list.

360
00:37:24,143 --> 00:37:26,698
(Politicians have allies and enemies.)

361
00:37:27,495 --> 00:37:28,997
(But I believe that…)

362
00:37:29,600 --> 00:37:31,151
(My enemies give me strength.)

363
00:37:31,446 --> 00:37:33,965
(And real friends give me courage.)

364
00:37:34,280 --> 00:37:38,101
From his criminal record,
he was involved in drug cases,

365
00:37:38,759 --> 00:37:40,597
bid rigging of state enterprises,

366
00:37:40,982 --> 00:37:42,003
and money laundering.

367
00:37:42,330 --> 00:37:43,799
There are nearly 10 cases in total.

368
00:37:44,173 --> 00:37:44,902
You’re right.

369
00:37:45,346 --> 00:37:48,999
There are also rumors that he’s involved
in scamming and human trafficking.

370
00:37:49,170 --> 00:37:50,649
All charges against him were dropped.

371
00:37:51,103 --> 00:37:52,298
All of them?

372
00:37:52,670 --> 00:37:53,452
Yes, sir.

373
00:37:54,820 --> 00:37:58,377
He made it through all that
because of his saintly image.

374
00:37:58,406 --> 00:38:00,413
(Hello. How adorable.)

375
00:38:00,461 --> 00:38:01,203
(Here.)

376
00:38:01,440 --> 00:38:05,498
I think he’s the most perfect candidate
for Nekros’s victim in Chapter 18.

377
00:38:07,110 --> 00:38:08,199
I agree with him.

378
00:38:10,969 --> 00:38:11,799
Listen to this.

379
00:38:12,340 --> 00:38:15,461
The MP is recently taking
a meditation retreat

380
00:38:15,485 --> 00:38:17,104
at a temple in the suburbs.

381
00:38:17,545 --> 00:38:21,850
This footage was posted on
the temple’s PR page just hours ago.

382
00:38:26,643 --> 00:38:27,501
Contact him.

383
00:38:27,803 --> 00:38:28,597
Immediately.

384
00:38:29,255 --> 00:38:32,800
Ugh, you’re giving me headaches.

385
00:38:33,015 --> 00:38:35,497
I’m telling you. Leave me alone.

386
00:38:35,690 --> 00:38:39,000
Don’t you get my name involved in
that stupid cartoon.

387
00:38:39,384 --> 00:38:40,600
And most importantly,

388
00:38:40,969 --> 00:38:44,800
if you stain my name in the press,

389
00:38:45,225 --> 00:38:47,010
I’ll sue the whole police department.

390
00:38:48,226 --> 00:38:50,101
Ugh, what the hell?

391
00:38:57,529 --> 00:38:58,202
Sir.

392
00:38:59,162 --> 00:39:02,997
I heard that the killer
has claimed three victims.

393
00:39:03,900 --> 00:39:06,102
Each victim was all high profile.

394
00:39:08,938 --> 00:39:10,199
You heard, you said?

395
00:39:10,359 --> 00:39:10,999
Yes.

396
00:39:12,890 --> 00:39:14,470
What the fuck are you waiting for, then?

397
00:39:16,001 --> 00:39:17,800
Crank up my security.

398
00:39:18,410 --> 00:39:19,204
Go!

399
00:39:21,372 --> 00:39:22,501
Idiot.

400
00:39:24,190 --> 00:39:25,399
Freaking idiot.

401
00:39:55,430 --> 00:39:57,696
Tell me if you find something suspicious.

402
00:39:59,218 --> 00:39:59,977
Yes, sir.

403
00:40:12,599 --> 00:40:14,298
You don’t have to go to work
tomorrow, do you?

404
00:40:15,924 --> 00:40:16,800
No.

405
00:40:17,776 --> 00:40:20,801
But I’m not pulling an all-nighter
with you, Inspector.

406
00:40:22,520 --> 00:40:24,695
If nothing comes up, you can go home soon.

407
00:40:25,050 --> 00:40:26,202
I’ll have another team relieve us.

408
00:40:38,330 --> 00:40:39,203
You hungry?

409
00:40:40,609 --> 00:40:41,498
I’m good.

410
00:40:53,275 --> 00:40:53,898
Hey.

411
00:40:54,525 --> 00:40:55,702
Can I ask you something?

412
00:40:56,505 --> 00:40:57,151
Yes?

413
00:40:58,660 --> 00:41:00,250
Why did you write Nekros?

414
00:41:06,941 --> 00:41:08,210
Is that question off limits?

415
00:41:15,810 --> 00:41:19,301
Would it be alright
if I refused to answer?

416
00:41:23,790 --> 00:41:24,751
It’s up to you.

417
00:41:47,661 --> 00:41:49,696
I wrote Nekros…

418
00:41:52,176 --> 00:41:53,803
From my life.

419
00:41:56,100 --> 00:41:57,495
My family was ruined

420
00:42:01,912 --> 00:42:05,101
because of the Thai Investment Bank case.

421
00:42:18,070 --> 00:42:19,097
My father

422
00:42:20,626 --> 00:42:22,490
was forced to take the blame.

423
00:42:24,620 --> 00:42:27,501
He spent his life calling for justice.

424
00:42:29,245 --> 00:42:30,500
But no one gave a damn.

425
00:42:32,691 --> 00:42:37,799
Even the law itself
couldn’t save him, Inspector.

426
00:42:41,300 --> 00:42:42,599
In the end,

427
00:42:42,800 --> 00:42:44,240
GIVE ME BACK MY MONEY / SCUM FAMILY

428
00:42:44,267 --> 00:42:45,930
he was left with a massive debt.

429
00:42:47,071 --> 00:42:47,984
He was cornered,

430
00:42:48,698 --> 00:42:49,797
helpless,

431
00:42:51,541 --> 00:42:54,295
and chose to end his problem by…

432
00:42:59,310 --> 00:43:00,297
Killing himself.

433
00:43:03,290 --> 00:43:05,000
Along with his whole family.

434
00:43:07,252 --> 00:43:08,100
Dad?

435
00:43:09,245 --> 00:43:10,078
Where are you?

436
00:43:10,108 --> 00:43:10,895
Mom!

437
00:43:11,195 --> 00:43:12,498
Dad!

438
00:43:12,726 --> 00:43:13,797
Mom!

439
00:43:15,254 --> 00:43:15,984
Dad!

440
00:43:16,585 --> 00:43:17,984
Help me!

441
00:43:26,370 --> 00:43:30,798
I created Nekros because of
my own despair in the justice system.

442
00:43:32,063 --> 00:43:33,802
Because a nobody like me

443
00:43:34,930 --> 00:43:36,396
can’t make a difference.

444
00:43:40,981 --> 00:43:42,501
But I’m serious, Inspector,

445
00:43:43,821 --> 00:43:49,983
if the justice system could have helped
my family even a little…

446
00:43:55,829 --> 00:43:57,900
My life wouldn’t have turned out this way.

447
00:44:08,685 --> 00:44:11,803
I understand why you’d think that way.

448
00:44:12,310 --> 00:44:13,402
But listen to me.

449
00:44:17,255 --> 00:44:20,300
I’ll prove to you

450
00:44:21,980 --> 00:44:22,904
that this world

451
00:44:24,372 --> 00:44:26,501
doesn’t need a monster like Nekros.

452
00:44:42,578 --> 00:44:43,897
Someone’s trying to break in.

453
00:44:44,155 --> 00:44:45,159
Get ready to seize him!

454
00:45:18,194 --> 00:45:18,901
Inspector.

455
00:45:19,630 --> 00:45:21,000
Why are you moving closer…?

456
00:45:22,387 --> 00:45:24,240
Are you going to put me
in handcuffs again?

457
00:45:25,340 --> 00:45:26,301
No, I’m not.

458
00:45:28,511 --> 00:45:29,400
Turn this way.

459
00:46:13,660 --> 00:46:14,600
Thank you.

460
00:46:16,520 --> 00:46:17,981
I’ll give you a ride home after we eat.

461
00:46:19,853 --> 00:46:20,700
Thank you.

462
00:46:34,881 --> 00:46:35,650
You’ve got good eyes.

463
00:46:35,865 --> 00:46:37,201
You remember all the details.

464
00:46:37,251 --> 00:46:39,130
No wonder your manga is famous.

465
00:46:42,140 --> 00:46:44,650
Lies end up being truths

466
00:46:45,071 --> 00:46:47,495
because the person who knows the truth
chooses to stay silent.

467
00:46:53,650 --> 00:46:56,400
If we’re successful in catching him,

468
00:46:57,030 --> 00:46:58,800
the rest of the manga
won’t be necessary anymore.

